29/09/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador to BiH Douglas McElhaney is again urging voters to go to the polls on Sunday (1 October), stressing the significance of these elections to the country's future.
In an interview in Friday's Nezavisne novine, McElhaney appealed particularly to young voters to cast ballots.
Principal Deputy High Representative to BiH Lawrence Butler issued a statement of his own, urging a high voter turnout and support for candidates ready to fight poverty, crime and corruption.
(Nezavisne novine - 29/09/06;
NTV Hayat - 28/09/06)
